        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 5:24PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Falconerville, or over Amherst, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Amherst...
Clifford...
Falconerville...
Riverville...
New Glasgow...
Oakville...
and Madison Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
